##Lightweight C Thread Pool Documentation
Project Overview
This is a pure C implementation of a thread pool based on the POSIX pthread library, specifically designed for embedded Linux systems. It provides simple and efficient multi-threaded task scheduling, solving the performance overhead of frequent thread creation/destruction and system resource exhaustion issues.
The code is concise, has no third-party dependencies, minimal memory footprint, and excellent portability. It is ideal for resource-constrained embedded devices such as Luckfox-Pico-Ultra and Raspberry Pi.
Core Features
✅ Fixed-size worker thread pool: Precise control over system concurrency
✅ Bounded task queue: Prevents memory overflow and enables graceful degradation under high load
✅ Two shutdown modes: Graceful wait-for-completion (shutdown_wait) and immediate termination (shutdown_now)
✅ Thread-safe: Robust synchronization with mutexes and condition variables
✅ Comprehensive error handling: All APIs return clear error codes
✅ Automatic resource management: No memory leaks
✅ Classic .h + .c separation: Easy integration into any C/C++ project
✅ Embedded-optimized: Minimized memory usage and CPU overhead
